Change `col-md-6` to `col-6` as this is Bootstrap&#39;s 4 smallest screen case. `col-md-6` will keep two columns next to each other on md (&gt;=768px) sized screens and larger, but stack them below that breakpoint. And you will need to [wrap that inner set of divs][1] in a div with the class row.

    &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col-md-4&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;col-6&quot;&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;col-6&quot;&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col-md-4&quot;&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col-md-4&quot;&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;


  [1]: https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/layout/grid/#nesting

